WEBVTT

00:03.133 --> 00:06.136
Today is our 10th
Friendiversary.

00:06.180 --> 00:10.227
10 years ago, four kids entereda Chuck E. Cheese ball pit

00:10.271 --> 00:13.839
as strangers,
but they emerged...

00:13.883 --> 00:15.319
[ Sniffles ]

00:15.363 --> 00:17.234
They emerged
best friends.

00:17.278 --> 00:19.758
[ Wailing ]

00:19.802 --> 00:22.283
I promised myself
I wouldn't do this!

00:22.326 --> 00:26.069
Let's skip the speech
and go straight to dessert.

00:26.113 --> 00:29.203
[ R&B music plays ]

00:29.246 --> 00:31.335
♪ In a Chuck E. Cheese

00:31.379 --> 00:34.338
♪ These four boys will meet

00:34.382 --> 00:38.125
♪ It's our Friendiversary

00:38.168 --> 00:40.083
♪ Friendiversary

00:40.127 --> 00:44.522
♪ We're Snot, we're Barry,
we're Steve, and Toshi ♪

00:44.566 --> 00:46.872
♪ It's our Friendiversary

00:46.916 --> 00:49.701
♪ Friendiversary

00:49.745 --> 00:56.447
♪ It's our
Friendiversary-y-y-y-y ♪

00:56.491 --> 00:59.363
Squash, squash, squash!
Squash, squash!

00:59.407 --> 01:01.322
Roger needs
a squash partner!

01:01.365 --> 01:02.758
-Roger!
-Steve!

01:02.801 --> 01:04.542
Big squash tourney
tomorrow.

01:04.586 --> 01:06.892
I need you to be
my squash partner.

01:06.936 --> 01:07.893
Squash.

01:07.937 --> 01:09.504
I don't even know
what squash is.

01:09.547 --> 01:11.810
What?!Everyone knows squash.

01:11.854 --> 01:13.203
-Roger.
-Squash.

01:13.247 --> 01:14.683
It's our Friendiversary.

01:14.726 --> 01:17.686
My week is jam-packed
with friendship activities.

01:17.729 --> 01:19.688
Jam-packed!

01:19.731 --> 01:21.342
But, Steve --

01:21.385 --> 01:23.344
I'm not gonna
ditch my friends.

01:23.387 --> 01:25.694
Sorry, you'll need to find
another squash partner.

01:25.737 --> 01:27.348
Everybody at the club
is paired up,

01:27.391 --> 01:30.177
and the club doesn't allow
blacks, Jews, or women.

01:30.220 --> 01:33.180
That rules out my tennis
partner, Rashika Greenblatt.

01:33.223 --> 01:36.270
The racism is thick, but so is
the club's lobster bisque,

01:36.313 --> 01:39.055
which is why
I'll never walk away.

01:39.099 --> 01:41.579
♪♪

01:41.623 --> 01:44.234
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.

01:44.278 --> 01:48.064
♪ I got a feelin' thatit's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

01:48.108 --> 01:51.198
♪ The sun in the sky
has a smile on his face ♪

01:51.241 --> 01:55.854
♪ And he's shinin' a salute
to the American race ♪

01:57.421 --> 02:00.598
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say

02:00.642 --> 02:03.384
♪ Good -- ♪ Good morning, U.S.A.

02:03.427 --> 02:04.385
Aah!

02:05.473 --> 02:09.041
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.

02:11.348 --> 02:13.742
If you have
the legendary shards,

02:13.785 --> 02:16.223
I recommend you visit Xur
on Titan

02:16.266 --> 02:18.790
and purchase the Wardcliff CoilRocket Launcher.

02:18.834 --> 02:20.227
[ Groans ]

02:20.270 --> 02:24.056
Then get the legendary shards,you [bleep] licking suckboy!

02:24.100 --> 02:25.232
Third graders.

02:25.275 --> 02:26.407
I can't believe it.

02:26.450 --> 02:28.191
I asked Steve
to play squash

02:28.235 --> 02:30.367
and he wouldn't cancel plans
with his friends.

02:30.411 --> 02:32.064
Those guys are tight,bro.

02:32.108 --> 02:33.979
They remind me of
my boys in Tampa.

02:34.023 --> 02:35.546
You don't have friends
in Tampa.

02:35.590 --> 02:37.331
[ Chuckling ]
Okay, pal.

02:37.374 --> 02:38.810
Then why do I
have a tattoo

02:38.854 --> 02:41.857
of an alligator in a bikinidriving down I-4?

02:41.900 --> 02:44.425
[ Man screams]Oh, you made me lose!

02:44.468 --> 02:48.255
Make him lose...
his friends.

02:48.298 --> 02:50.474
Excellent idea, Klaus!

02:50.518 --> 02:51.997
[ Woman shouting indistinctly]

02:52.041 --> 02:55.479
Slow down, lady.
Your son is a liar.

02:55.523 --> 02:56.611
What?!

02:56.654 --> 02:58.265
He was the one swearing at me,

02:58.308 --> 03:00.354
and he made a Chinese joke!

03:00.397 --> 03:01.442
[ Shouting continues ]

03:01.485 --> 03:04.271
Oh, w-- Well, I'm Chinese, too!

03:04.314 --> 03:08.275
[ Urinating, humming ]

03:08.318 --> 03:10.581
Man,
look at the splash back.

03:10.625 --> 03:12.583
Got that
Super Soaker thrust.

03:12.627 --> 03:14.803
You're just painting those
Entertainment Weekly's

03:14.846 --> 03:16.631
in the magazine rack.[ Zips pants ]

03:16.674 --> 03:18.720
Your flattery won't get meto play squash.

03:18.763 --> 03:20.330
Squ-what?
[ Laughs ]

03:20.374 --> 03:22.027
I haven't thought about that
in ages.

03:22.071 --> 03:24.291
You seemed really into it,like, 10 minutes ago.

03:24.334 --> 03:27.381
Speaking of minutes ago,

03:27.424 --> 03:29.600
how many has it been
since Barry ate?

03:29.644 --> 03:31.820
What a fat guy,
don't you think?

03:31.863 --> 03:33.300
He does struggle
with weight,

03:33.343 --> 03:36.259
but I love my Care Bare,big or small.

03:36.303 --> 03:37.826
Speaking of small,

03:37.869 --> 03:40.481
what about Snot's bank account,am I right?

03:40.524 --> 03:44.267
Oh, Snotter, so poor in money,so rich in character.

03:44.311 --> 03:45.486
You're impossible.

03:45.529 --> 03:46.661
I'm not gonna
keep recording over

03:46.704 --> 03:49.054
all my great business ideas
for this crap.

03:49.098 --> 03:52.841
Roger: A novelty device that  transforms Julia Child's voice

03:52.884 --> 03:55.278
into a deep,
scary monster voice.

03:55.322 --> 03:56.845
Oh, wait.
Oh, wait, did I miss my stop?

03:56.888 --> 03:59.195
I'm looking for
the ferry to Alcatraz.

03:59.239 --> 04:00.979
Or is it swimmable?
I'm on a budget.

04:01.023 --> 04:03.199
This is my first time
in San Francisco.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.853
That's not true.
Why did I say that?

04:04.896 --> 04:08.291
I almost lost this
because of you!

04:12.687 --> 04:14.166
This is
pretty interesting.

04:14.210 --> 04:16.734
Four 12-year-old kidsdesigned a computer

04:16.778 --> 04:18.649
that destroyed
all of Cincinnati.

04:18.693 --> 04:20.521
-Wow.
-Oh, misread it.

04:20.564 --> 04:22.653
It was 412 1-year-olds.

04:22.697 --> 04:24.438
That's a lot
less interesting.

04:24.481 --> 04:26.091
You guys aren't gonna
believe this.

04:26.135 --> 04:27.310
Jeff has a talent!

04:27.354 --> 04:28.659
-Bullshit.
-It's true.

04:28.703 --> 04:30.487
We were just watchingthe house-renovation show

04:30.531 --> 04:33.098
"Flip or Flop,"and Jeff knew when to flip

04:33.142 --> 04:34.665
and he knew when to flop.

04:34.709 --> 04:35.579
I did.

04:35.623 --> 04:37.320
How is this possible?

04:37.364 --> 04:39.888
Mom, when you look around
the house, what do you see?

04:39.931 --> 04:41.455
Walls.

04:41.498 --> 04:42.499
Just a lot of walls.

04:42.543 --> 04:44.893
[ Scoffs ] Walls.
What a noob.

04:44.936 --> 04:47.156
What do we see, Jeff,you and I?

04:47.199 --> 04:49.114
When I look at a house,

04:49.158 --> 04:51.465
I can see
beyond the walls...

04:51.508 --> 04:53.684
-Uh-huh.
-...above the ceiling...

04:53.728 --> 04:55.904
-That's right.
-...and below the floor.

04:55.947 --> 04:59.516
-Bingo.
-I can see its bones.

04:59.560 --> 05:01.126
Happy now, Francine?

05:01.170 --> 05:04.129
If we combine his instincts
with your money,

05:04.173 --> 05:05.479
the sky's the limit.

05:05.522 --> 05:07.350
The sky, you say?

05:08.525 --> 05:11.833
He's surveying
the bones of our house.

05:11.876 --> 05:14.357
He is? Well,
don't hold out on us, Jeff.

05:14.401 --> 05:15.402
What do you see?

05:15.445 --> 05:19.406
[ Breathes deeply ]

05:19.449 --> 05:23.584
Your house
has great bones.

05:23.627 --> 05:26.413
-[ Sighs ]
-Wow, he's good.

05:26.456 --> 05:28.371
Do me, do me!
How are my bones?

05:28.415 --> 05:29.720
[ Breathes deeply ]

05:29.764 --> 05:33.158
You're not a house,
Mr. S.

05:33.202 --> 05:35.813
A goddamn master.

05:38.425 --> 05:40.601
Kick those legs,
Barry!

05:40.644 --> 05:42.907
I can't do it!
Swan!

05:43.778 --> 05:46.171
I'll never learn to swim.

05:46.215 --> 05:47.956
[ Coaxingly ] Barry.

05:47.999 --> 05:49.610
Barry.

05:49.653 --> 05:51.089
[ Chuckles ]

05:51.133 --> 05:52.526
Stop making me laugh.

05:52.569 --> 05:54.223
There's that smile!

05:54.266 --> 05:56.965
Aww, I love you guys.

05:57.008 --> 06:00.403
Steve, I set up a cabana
and filled it with strippers.

06:00.447 --> 06:01.752
Roger, go away.

06:01.796 --> 06:03.624
It's Friendiversary
swim day.

06:03.667 --> 06:07.236
Why don't you come over here
and swim into some strange?

06:07.279 --> 06:10.413
This is Steve, the underage boyI was telling you about.

06:10.457 --> 06:12.023
You really don't get it,huh?

06:12.067 --> 06:13.677
These are my friends,

06:13.721 --> 06:15.462
and I'll neverturn my back on them.

06:15.505 --> 06:17.507
You can tell yourself that,
but you'll slip up,

06:17.551 --> 06:19.422
just like I told myself I was
never gonna see

06:19.466 --> 06:21.555
another Woody Allen movie,
but there I was,

06:21.598 --> 06:23.426
first in line
for "Blue Jasmine."

06:23.470 --> 06:25.994
So boring, so good.

06:26.037 --> 06:27.561
[ Dog barking,
siren wailing in distance ]

06:27.604 --> 06:29.606
This neighborhood
looks kind of seedy.

06:29.650 --> 06:32.435
Is that a Satanic church
next door?

06:32.479 --> 06:34.219
They practice Santería.

06:34.263 --> 06:38.223
I don't know the difference,but I'm told there is one.

06:38.267 --> 06:40.661
Has anyone died in here?

06:40.704 --> 06:42.445
It feels like
someone died in here.

06:42.489 --> 06:43.794
No! God no.

06:43.838 --> 06:45.883
The last owner was stabbed
in the house,

06:45.927 --> 06:49.496
but he managed to crawl
to the lawn before he died.

06:49.539 --> 06:51.454
Jeff,
tell us about the house.

06:51.498 --> 06:56.154
Quite possibly the greatest
bones I've ever seen.

06:56.198 --> 06:58.505
Let's see them bones!

06:58.548 --> 07:00.681
What the hell
are you doing?!

07:00.724 --> 07:02.683
You know what?
Screw it.

07:02.726 --> 07:05.033
I'm quitting
this industry.

07:05.076 --> 07:09.690
I have quit a lot of industries,though.

07:09.733 --> 07:11.039
I'm reconsidering.

07:11.082 --> 07:14.695
Guess what.
I'm back, babies!

07:14.738 --> 07:17.262
Aah!

07:17.306 --> 07:20.048
You know what?
I'm quitting this body.

07:20.091 --> 07:23.747
I have quit a lot of bodies,
though.

07:23.791 --> 07:25.619
I'm reconsidering.

07:25.662 --> 07:29.318
[ Screaming ]

07:30.580 --> 07:32.887
10 years ago,
we met within the hallowed

07:32.930 --> 07:36.281
and ultimately unprofitable
walls of this Chuck E. Cheese.

07:36.325 --> 07:39.415
The ball pit gave life
to our friendship.

07:39.459 --> 07:41.678
But it also gave life
to a super fungus

07:41.722 --> 07:43.680
that blinded an entire
Little League team

07:43.724 --> 07:45.508
and closed the doors
forever.

07:45.552 --> 07:48.293
And now we immortalize
our friendship

07:48.337 --> 07:50.121
with some
light vandalism.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.652
Ugh, Toshi,
that sucks.

07:58.695 --> 08:00.088
Announcer: That's right, Banksy.

08:00.131 --> 08:02.699
"American Dad's"
calling you a hack!

08:02.743 --> 08:04.919
Reveal your identity
and fight us.

08:04.962 --> 08:07.182
"American Dad" --
We are...

08:09.401 --> 08:13.231
[ Gravely voice ]
Who disturbs my slumber?

08:13.275 --> 08:15.538
[ Boys screaming ]

08:15.582 --> 08:17.148
Aah!

08:17.192 --> 08:19.890
You vandalized
my beautiful home!

08:19.934 --> 08:21.326
It wasn't my idea!

08:21.370 --> 08:23.546
Uh, Snot, Barry, and Toshimade me do it!

08:23.590 --> 08:25.679
[ Julia Child's voice ]
Whoa, you turned on
your friends so fast.

08:25.722 --> 08:27.419
I didn't even get to...

08:27.463 --> 08:29.770
[ Gravely voice ] ...clamp
your balls in a mouse trap.

08:29.813 --> 08:31.249
Clamp their balls,
not mine!

08:31.293 --> 08:34.252
T-They can't be far.I'll -- I'll help you find them.

08:34.296 --> 08:36.690
Toshi lives closest.I say we go there first.

08:36.733 --> 08:39.344
[ Gasps ]And we can trap Barrywith food.

08:39.388 --> 08:42.130
He'll eat himself to deathlike a goldfish.

08:42.173 --> 08:44.175
There's a lot of fightin Snot,

08:44.219 --> 08:45.829
but we can nab himwhen he's weakest --

08:45.873 --> 08:48.223
right afterhe sells his plasma.

08:48.266 --> 08:51.139
Nah,
I've got rat stuff to do.

08:51.182 --> 08:53.620
Good luck digging yourself
out of this hole, Steve.

08:53.663 --> 08:55.360
How do you know
my name?

08:55.404 --> 08:56.579
Uh...

08:56.623 --> 08:58.625
[ Julia Child's voice ]
Chuck E. Cheese knows

08:58.668 --> 09:00.322
all the children's names.

09:04.195 --> 09:08.504
So...should we report the guy inthe rat costume

09:08.548 --> 09:09.766
assaulting kids?
[ Chuckles ]

09:09.810 --> 09:13.857
I'm more concerned about
the rat in the guy costume

09:13.901 --> 09:15.598
assaulting friendships.

09:15.642 --> 09:17.731
-Snotter --
-Don't Snotter me.

09:17.774 --> 09:19.167
You betrayed us!

09:19.210 --> 09:23.214
I haven't felt this betrayedsince "Scrubs" moved to ABC!

09:23.258 --> 09:26.261
How old were you
when that happened?

09:26.304 --> 09:30.395
Well, how old am I now and whenwas that, and now subtract.

09:30.439 --> 09:31.875
Think, Snot.
Think!

09:31.919 --> 09:35.618
This bad blood --
this is on you!

09:39.013 --> 09:40.101
Snot, please take me back
as a friend.

09:40.144 --> 09:41.798
I can't get Bluetooth to sync,

09:41.842 --> 09:44.888
but pretend it's playing
your favorite Matisyahu song.

09:44.932 --> 09:46.455
So I should just pretend

09:46.498 --> 09:50.198
his entire catalogue is playingat the same time?

09:50.241 --> 09:51.416
Fat chance!

09:51.460 --> 09:55.377
You backstabbed usduring Friendiversary!

09:58.249 --> 09:59.511
0-for-3.

09:59.555 --> 10:02.776
I'd say you're 3-for-3
at losing your friends.

10:02.819 --> 10:04.081
Perfect record, bud.

10:04.125 --> 10:06.214
Thanks for puttinga positive spin on it.

10:06.257 --> 10:08.477
Looks like you'rethe only friend I have left.

10:08.520 --> 10:11.654
We all make mistakes, but life
is like a game of squash.

10:11.698 --> 10:12.829
You got to
keep on whackin'.

10:12.873 --> 10:15.136
I forgot all about
your tournament.

10:15.179 --> 10:15.919
Rotten Steve!

10:15.963 --> 10:17.486
You stop that right now.

10:17.529 --> 10:19.880
I doubt there's even time
to enter the tournament.

10:19.923 --> 10:22.273
Well,
we could make the cutoff.

10:22.317 --> 10:24.145
But we wouldn't be able to
take my friend Nancy's

10:24.188 --> 10:26.016
hot aerobics class
before.

10:26.060 --> 10:27.365
Would you
be willing to play

10:27.409 --> 10:29.367
without taking Nancy's
hot aerobics, Steve?

10:29.411 --> 10:31.152
Honestly,
we won't be as loose.

10:31.195 --> 10:33.850
Okay.I'll be your squash partner.

10:33.894 --> 10:36.026
You're giving me a second chance
at friendship,

10:36.070 --> 10:38.376
and this time,I'm gonna do it right.

10:38.420 --> 10:40.335
Oh!
-You're doing it wrong!

10:40.378 --> 10:42.337
Damn it, Steve,
clear a path!

10:42.380 --> 10:43.730
You got it, friend.

10:43.773 --> 10:45.079
Get a clue, Steve.

10:45.122 --> 10:46.776
[Bleep]

10:46.820 --> 10:48.604
Well played, Chip.
Your serve.

10:48.648 --> 10:51.476
Hey, Rog, the kid'sall covered in welts.

10:51.520 --> 10:53.087
-Your serve, Chip.
-How about we call it?

10:53.130 --> 10:54.479
How about you serve,
Chip?

10:54.523 --> 10:55.916
[ Sighs ]

10:55.959 --> 10:58.658
Okay, Steve, clear that path
and we got this.

11:01.182 --> 11:06.970
[ Slow motion ]
Clear a path!

11:09.320 --> 11:11.279
Path!

11:11.322 --> 11:13.890
Clear it!

11:15.413 --> 11:16.327
Aah!

11:16.371 --> 11:18.112
[Bleep]

11:19.983 --> 11:22.769
Hell of a game.
Nice backhand today, Bob.

11:22.812 --> 11:23.987
My partner
just didn't have it.

11:24.031 --> 11:25.554
Is he gonna be okay?

11:25.597 --> 11:26.729
Are you gonna be okay?

11:26.773 --> 11:28.949
Hey, you just worry about
the next round.

11:28.992 --> 11:30.864
Go win this thing.

11:30.907 --> 11:33.562
What are we doing next?

11:33.605 --> 11:34.824
I don't understand.

11:34.868 --> 11:36.173
You're acting like
we're friends,

11:36.217 --> 11:39.002
but you're bad at squash.
What am I missing here?

11:39.046 --> 11:40.961
You're missing
high-quality backpacks

11:41.004 --> 11:42.919
made out of
recycled materials!

11:42.963 --> 11:44.747
-I am?
-[ Mockingly ] "I am?"

11:44.791 --> 11:45.879
[ Laughs ]
Just kidding.

11:45.922 --> 11:47.358
Step inside.
I'll hook you up.

11:47.402 --> 11:49.230
-Steve, I'm gonna do this.
-I'll come with.

11:49.273 --> 11:50.884
[ Mockingly ] "I'll come with."[ Laughs ]

11:50.927 --> 11:53.974
You're worse than this guy.
-You stay.

11:54.017 --> 11:55.932
You are really funny.

11:58.892 --> 12:00.371
[ Dog barking ]

12:02.156 --> 12:04.375
They don't make bones like thisanymore.

12:04.419 --> 12:06.334
Damn right.
So, what's the next step?

12:06.377 --> 12:09.250
Renovations?
-And cover up these bones?

12:09.293 --> 12:12.644
Mr. S, are you the stupidestperson I've ever met?

12:12.688 --> 12:14.429
-Jeff!
-No, he's right.

12:14.472 --> 12:16.387
I spoke out of turn.
Go on, Jeff.

12:16.431 --> 12:18.563
It's time to
flip this house,

12:18.607 --> 12:22.611
and I recommend we only considerall-cash offers.

12:22.654 --> 12:25.266
A goddamn master.

12:27.834 --> 12:28.791
[ Groans ]

12:28.835 --> 12:30.575
I wish you weren't married,
Chip.

12:30.619 --> 12:33.448
I bet your wife doesn't do this,Chip.

12:33.491 --> 12:34.928
[ Warbling ]

12:34.971 --> 12:37.017
Wakey, wakey.

12:37.060 --> 12:38.714
I made you
breakfast in bed.

12:38.758 --> 12:40.585
It's cold because
it's almost dinnertime.

12:40.629 --> 12:43.153
-Okay, we need to talk.
-Best friend talk.

12:43.197 --> 12:45.373
-Shut up and listen to me.
-Best friend listen.

12:45.416 --> 12:47.679
Our so-called "friendship"was based on

12:47.723 --> 12:51.074
a mutual love of squash,which you didn't share.

12:51.118 --> 12:52.380
This is over.

12:52.423 --> 12:54.164
But --
But you're my only friend!

12:54.208 --> 12:55.949
No.
Now clear a path.

12:55.992 --> 12:57.951
Sure thing, buddy.
[ Laughs ]

12:57.994 --> 13:00.431
See?
We can make this work.

13:00.475 --> 13:02.956
You've got a clingy friend
on your hands, bro.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.609
[ Scoffs ]I'm gonna head over to the pier

13:04.653 --> 13:06.394
and work onmy robot man routine.

13:06.437 --> 13:08.613
Everything will be normalby the time I get back.

13:08.657 --> 13:11.965
Ahh, there's so many sick piers
in Tampa.

13:12.008 --> 13:13.618
My boy Vance
basically lives there.

13:13.662 --> 13:16.621
He makes bank selling
butterfly knives to tourists.

13:16.665 --> 13:18.885
Nobody believesyou have friends in Tampa.

13:20.016 --> 13:23.846
Oh, yeah? Then where did I get
skin cancer, smart guy?

13:23.890 --> 13:26.414
[ Coaster riders screaming ]

13:26.457 --> 13:30.070
Beep, boop,
beep, beep, boop.

13:30.113 --> 13:31.985
Beep, boop, boop, beep...

13:32.028 --> 13:33.900
Dad,
that robot wants money.

13:33.943 --> 13:36.990
...beep, beep,
boop, boop, beep...

13:37.033 --> 13:39.862
Stay away from him.
These guys have diseases.

13:39.906 --> 13:41.037
Shut up!
You don't know me.

13:41.081 --> 13:43.126
You're just
a lucky guesser.

13:43.170 --> 13:44.693
Beep, boop, beep --

13:44.736 --> 13:47.348
I'm Robot Man's best friend,
Gold Boy.

13:47.391 --> 13:48.697
[ Whispering ]
It's me -- Steve.

13:48.740 --> 13:50.525
[ Robot voice ]
Get lost, Gold Boy.

13:50.568 --> 13:52.135
[ Normal voice ]
No can do.

13:52.179 --> 13:54.268
I'm your sidekick
for all eternity.

13:54.311 --> 13:56.096
[ Whispering ]
And in real life, too.

13:56.139 --> 13:57.749
-Beep, boop!
-Aah!

13:57.793 --> 14:01.101
Beep.

14:01.144 --> 14:03.059
[ Knock on door ]

14:03.103 --> 14:05.148
Hello! Welcome.

14:05.192 --> 14:07.107
So, it's protective bootiesfor everyone.

14:07.150 --> 14:09.065
I'm sure you've noticedthe bones.
Huh?

14:09.109 --> 14:10.806
So, we're asking
potential buyers

14:10.850 --> 14:13.940
for a heartfelt letter outliningwhy you should get the house.

14:13.983 --> 14:17.030
Sorry, I thought
this house was abandoned.

14:17.073 --> 14:18.683
See,
my girlfriend has diarrhea,

14:18.727 --> 14:20.772
and I wanted to
shoot up a little.

14:22.209 --> 14:24.124
Damn it!No one wants this house.

14:24.167 --> 14:27.127
Nobody cares about bones.

14:27.170 --> 14:28.737
Jeff screwed us!

14:28.780 --> 14:30.565
Jeffrey,
is this true?

14:30.608 --> 14:31.827
Did you screw us?

14:31.871 --> 14:33.307
Looks like I did,
Mr. S.

14:33.350 --> 14:35.048
Okay,
you can kill him.

14:35.091 --> 14:36.484
Run, babe!

14:36.527 --> 14:39.879
We're all gonna needfresh booties to go back in!

14:42.142 --> 14:45.145
[ Gargling ]

14:45.188 --> 14:47.712
I can't
get rid of Steve.

14:47.756 --> 14:50.759
[ Chuckles ]Courtney, my boy in Tampa,

14:50.802 --> 14:51.978
he had a clinger like this.

14:52.021 --> 14:53.718
Florida State girl.

14:53.762 --> 14:54.763
You know how that goes.

14:54.806 --> 14:56.330
Actually, I don't,
and neither do you

14:56.373 --> 14:58.201
because none of those people
exist.

14:58.245 --> 14:59.768
I have an actual crisis!

14:59.811 --> 15:01.117
What did you expect?

15:01.161 --> 15:04.599
You blew up his entire supportsystem for a squash partner.

15:04.642 --> 15:06.079
[ Doorknob rattles ]Steve: Roger, you in there?

15:06.122 --> 15:07.123
You going wee-wee?

15:07.167 --> 15:08.211
What do I do, Klaus?

15:08.255 --> 15:10.083
Instead of losing Steve,

15:10.126 --> 15:14.174
you should be reuniting himwith his old friends.

15:14.217 --> 15:16.741
[ Drill whirs ]

15:16.785 --> 15:18.047
Peek-a-boo!

15:18.091 --> 15:19.092
Aah!

15:19.135 --> 15:20.441
You got me, buddy!

15:20.484 --> 15:22.617
How can I reunite Steve
and his friends?

15:22.660 --> 15:25.185
Well, to learn about that, youhave to learn about friendship,

15:25.228 --> 15:27.143
and if you want tolearn about friendship,

15:27.187 --> 15:29.537
we have to go
to Tampa.

15:29.580 --> 15:31.756
There's no way
you have friends in Tampa.

15:31.800 --> 15:34.237
But a little trip to get away
from Steve, I'm in.

15:34.281 --> 15:36.544
Pack for the heat.You got any tank tops?

15:36.587 --> 15:39.416
I have a framed sleeveless
Aaron Rodgers jersey.

15:39.460 --> 15:41.549
Hmm.Do you own a glass cutter?

15:41.592 --> 15:43.594
I do,
but it's also framed.

15:43.638 --> 15:44.813
Okay, grab both frames

15:44.856 --> 15:47.207
and we'll figure it outon the way to the airport.

15:49.905 --> 15:54.344
♪♪

15:54.388 --> 15:55.867
[ Cellphone chimes ]

15:55.911 --> 15:57.391
Steve won't stop texting.

15:57.434 --> 15:59.828
"In line at
a goat cheese sale.

15:59.871 --> 16:01.134
Pick you up a log?"

16:01.177 --> 16:03.005
Can you believe
this guy?

16:03.049 --> 16:04.267
"Two logs."

16:04.311 --> 16:05.486
Relax.

16:05.529 --> 16:08.141
Steve just has toreunite with his old friends,

16:08.184 --> 16:10.621
and once you see how tight
me and my boys are,

16:10.665 --> 16:12.884
you'll know how to
make that happen.

16:12.928 --> 16:17.019
Now stop worrying and take inthese Florida swamps.

16:17.063 --> 16:19.239
Wow,
so these are the people

16:19.282 --> 16:21.676
who decide who's president
every time.

16:21.719 --> 16:25.027
We gon' make Hulk Hogan
president!

16:25.071 --> 16:27.073
You know best!

16:30.293 --> 16:31.816
There's a doorbell.

16:31.860 --> 16:34.036
[ Electricity crackles,
sour notes play ]

16:34.080 --> 16:35.516
When you show up
at a friend's house,

16:35.559 --> 16:38.258
make sure you bring
a fancy gift.

16:38.301 --> 16:40.695
Here, give these blunt wraps
to Big Ed.

16:40.738 --> 16:42.697
You're gonna
love these dudes.

16:42.740 --> 16:44.220
They're so funny.

16:45.526 --> 16:46.962
'Sup?

16:47.006 --> 16:49.182
'Sup?

16:49.225 --> 16:51.184
Whoa, no way.

16:51.227 --> 16:53.838
Your friends arereal.

16:53.882 --> 16:57.233
Look at this. There's an inside,and more guys!

16:57.277 --> 16:59.540
This is my boy, Roger.
He's chill.

16:59.583 --> 17:01.324
He's here to learn about
friendship.

17:01.368 --> 17:03.109
-'Sup?
-'Sup?

17:03.152 --> 17:05.720
Whoa, Klaus' storiesare for real?

17:05.763 --> 17:08.897
I can't believe it.Astroturf rug -- check.

17:08.940 --> 17:12.074
Unlicensedexotic animal storage -- check.

17:12.118 --> 17:13.249
The fan that's never on

17:13.293 --> 17:16.513
despite it being120 degrees in here -- check.

17:16.557 --> 17:19.212
But surely the torn posterwas a work of fiction.

17:19.255 --> 17:21.344
[ Gasps ]
The torn poster!

17:21.388 --> 17:23.216
In all its glory.

17:23.259 --> 17:26.654
Please, please take me tothe toilet Big Ed cracked

17:26.697 --> 17:28.264
when he sat on it
backwards.

17:28.308 --> 17:30.353
What the hell
are you doing out there?

17:30.397 --> 17:32.138
What? I was chill.

17:32.181 --> 17:33.313
Was I not chill?

17:33.356 --> 17:35.315
No,
you're being all crazy.

17:35.358 --> 17:36.751
What was that bullshit
about the fan?

17:36.794 --> 17:38.709
I told you that
in confidence.

17:38.753 --> 17:39.710
Okay, sorry.

17:39.754 --> 17:41.364
[ Sighs ]
I'm chill now.

17:41.408 --> 17:44.106
[ Snake hissing ]Holy [bleep] is thatthe water moccasin

17:44.150 --> 17:47.153
Vance took to the Orlandopremier of "Scary Movie 4"?!

17:47.196 --> 17:48.893
Pull yourself together,
man.

17:48.937 --> 17:51.331
Grab a room-temperature Otterpopfrom the lighter drawer

17:51.374 --> 17:53.898
and just...cool out.

17:53.942 --> 17:56.379
I'll go try to smooth it over
with the guys.

17:56.423 --> 17:59.339
Roger,
where are you going?

17:59.382 --> 18:01.167
We haven't solved
your Steve problem.

18:01.210 --> 18:04.039
I thinkI got my problem solved.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.128
[ Engine starts ]

18:06.172 --> 18:08.217
♪ Y'all gon' make me
lose my mind ♪

18:08.261 --> 18:09.392
♪ Up in here

18:11.568 --> 18:13.353
My mom and dad
are gonna kill us!

18:13.396 --> 18:15.268
Francine: These walls
won't hold forever!

18:15.311 --> 18:16.269
[ Sledgehammer slamming ]

18:16.312 --> 18:18.140
This is all my fault,babe.

18:18.184 --> 18:21.361
I never knew anythingabout flipping houses.

18:21.404 --> 18:25.016
I just wantedto be closer to you.

18:25.060 --> 18:26.409
Oh, babe.

18:26.453 --> 18:28.716
I love you
for who you are.

18:28.759 --> 18:31.936
Old-Timey Narrator:
And so ends

18:31.980 --> 18:36.245
the greatest love story
ever told.

18:36.289 --> 18:37.986
♪♪

18:38.029 --> 18:40.293
♪ Y'all gon' make me
act a fool ♪

18:40.336 --> 18:41.381
♪ Up in here, up in here

18:41.424 --> 18:43.644
Roger,
you returned to me!

18:43.687 --> 18:45.428
♪ Y'all gon' make me
lose my cool ♪

18:45.472 --> 18:46.516
♪ Up in here, up in here

18:46.560 --> 18:48.431
-Whose car is this?
-Buckle up.

18:48.475 --> 18:50.738
We're going to
a Friendiversary event.

18:50.781 --> 18:52.653
Oh, those guysdon't want to see me.

18:52.696 --> 18:54.045
Of course
they want to see you.

18:54.089 --> 18:56.091
You're gonna save their lives.
-Huh?

18:56.135 --> 18:58.659
♪ 'Cause you a soft type --
What ♪

18:58.702 --> 19:01.401
I figured out how to reunite youwith your friends.

19:01.444 --> 19:03.751
♪ Dog is a dog,
blood's thicker than water ♪

19:03.794 --> 19:06.536
I put a water moccasin
into the Chesterbrook pool,

19:06.580 --> 19:09.017
and then I invited your friendsto play Marco Polo

19:09.060 --> 19:10.975
with Olympic great
Michael Phelps.

19:11.019 --> 19:13.326
People will believe anything
in a Facebook invite.

19:13.369 --> 19:14.762
Fake news!

19:14.805 --> 19:16.459
Oh, my God,why would you do that?!

19:16.503 --> 19:20.376
So you can save their lives
and prove your loyalty.

19:20.420 --> 19:22.335
[ Tires screech ]

19:22.378 --> 19:24.467
Go get your friends back.

19:24.511 --> 19:26.339
When Michael Phelps
shows up,

19:26.382 --> 19:29.385
please don't tell himI'm sitting on six pool noodles.

19:29.429 --> 19:31.431
[ Panting ]
Get out of the pool!

19:31.474 --> 19:32.910
There's a deadly snake!

19:32.954 --> 19:34.434
Save it, Steve.

19:34.477 --> 19:35.391
I know I betrayed you,

19:35.435 --> 19:36.784
but you got to believe me!

19:36.827 --> 19:38.089
Save it.

19:38.133 --> 19:40.483
You don't need to pretendto save our lives.

19:40.527 --> 19:43.007
We already forgive you,Steve.

19:43.051 --> 19:44.444
What?
Y-You do?

19:44.487 --> 19:45.706
We got to talking,

19:45.749 --> 19:48.012
and a giant rat
grabbing us,

19:48.056 --> 19:49.710
we all would've blabbed.

19:54.149 --> 19:56.804
I can't believe
I got my best friends back.

19:56.847 --> 19:59.023
You were saying somethingabout a snake?

19:59.067 --> 20:00.503
Oh, my God, the snake!

20:00.547 --> 20:02.244
Roger:
What's taking so long?

20:02.288 --> 20:05.247
[ Hisses ]

20:05.291 --> 20:06.727
Loud batch of Natty Ice.

20:06.770 --> 20:08.642
Oh, I dumped the wrong cooler.

20:08.685 --> 20:11.384
There's no snake in here.

20:11.427 --> 20:14.387
Roger must've lied
to reunite us.

20:14.430 --> 20:16.215
Barry: Guys, look!
I'm swimming!

20:18.521 --> 20:21.307
It's a Friendiversary miracle!

20:21.350 --> 20:23.483
Snake!

20:23.526 --> 20:25.746
[ Screams ]

20:27.704 --> 20:28.879
Man down!

20:30.446 --> 20:33.101
We need to find the biteand suck out the venom!

20:34.581 --> 20:36.365
All: Ooh!

20:36.409 --> 20:38.324
Inner thigh.

20:38.367 --> 20:40.500
[ Sighs ]
I'll do it.

20:40.543 --> 20:42.415
No.
We're best friends,

20:42.458 --> 20:46.070
and we'll all
suck out the venom.

20:46.114 --> 20:50.858
♪♪

20:50.901 --> 20:53.991
Roger: I think I finally
understand friendship.

20:54.035 --> 20:56.429
Old-Timey Narrator:
And so ends

20:56.472 --> 21:02.173
the greatest love story
ever told.

21:02.217 --> 21:04.132
Have a great night!
